    "description": "Grow your career with Sarovar Hotels Capital India! We are hiring a Reservation Manager for our Vijayawada team. Be part of a workplace that celebrates innovation, diversity, and performance.\n\nAbout Sarovar Hotels Capital India:\nSarovar Hotels Capital India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Ensure compliance with FSSAI, health, and safety regulations\n• Prepare daily operating reports and present to management\n• Deliver exceptional guest experiences in line with brand standards\n• Develop and maintain relationships with corporate clients\n• Train and supervise front-line staff on service standards\n• Manage front office operations including check-in/check-out\n• Manage procurement of hotel supplies and control operating costs\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 12-20 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Front Office\n• Proficiency in Revenue Management\n• Proficiency in GDS Systems\n• Proficiency in MICE\n• Proficiency in Crisis Management\n• Proficiency in Hotel Management\n• Proficiency in Housekeeping Standards\n• Proficiency in Opera PMS\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 35 LPA - 70 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Sarovar Hotels Capital India!",
